"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44150","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-24","<p /> <p /> <p>There are approximately 50 DWP staff working on the enhanced Universal Credit service. </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-03-24T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44150/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44150/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-19",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many full-time equivalent staff in his Department are working on developing the enhanced Universal Credit IT system.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","192757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44151","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-24","<p>As part of the wider transformation of its services, the Department is developing an enhanced digital service for Universal Credit. As part of our commitment to testing Universal Credit as it develops, we expect to trial an early version of the enhanced digital service to a limited number of claimants later this year.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-03-24T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44151/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44151/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-19",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects the first alternative Universal Credit digital service to be in use in a job centre.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","192759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44153","Department for Education","false","2014-03-26","<p>We have not yet made final decisions on what the entitlement criteria for free school meals under Universal Credit will be. We are working with the Department for Work and Pensions to develop suitable criteria which will ensure that free lunches continue to be available to those families on the lowest incomes.</p><p>We will allow good time for interested parties to comment on our proposals before we introduce the new criteria.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-03-26T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44153/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44153/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-03-19",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, at what level of household income children in households in receipt of universal credit will be eligible for free school meals.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","192826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44154","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-25","<p> </p><p>The information requested is published and can be found in the table entitled “Housing Benefit” at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/273833/outturn-and-forecast-expenditure-201213.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/273833/outturn-and-forecast-expenditure-201213.xls</a></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-03-25T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44154/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/44154/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-19",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of total Government expenditure on housing benefit in (a) cash and (b) real terms in each of the last 30 years.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","192828"
