"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42243","Home Office","false","2014-04-02","<p> </p><p>The total number of passengers who travelled to the UK on routes connected to <br>the Semaphore system were approximately as follows:<br><br>(a) 66.5 million in 2011<br><br>(b) 64.5 million in 2012<br><br>(c) 78.8 million in 2013</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42243/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42243/answer",,,,,"1",,,"2014-03-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many passengers travelled to the UK on routes connected to the Semaphore system in (a) 2011, (b) 2012 and (c) 2013.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","191338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42248","Home Office","false","2014-04-01","<p> </p><p>16 victims of trafficking (1 male, 15 female) have received financial <br>assistance under the programme since April 2011.<br><br>While the Assisted Voluntary Return for Irregular Migrants (AVRIM) programme <br>does not normally include financial assistance, a discretionary sum of up to <br>£1000 is provided for specified vulnerable cases, and this includes victims of <br>trafficking. Assisted Voluntary Return is only available to non-EEA nationals <br>and the support is not dependent upon whether the individual has arrived from <br>inside or outside the EU.<br><br>The figures provided are sourced from a Home Office management information <br>system which is not quality assured under National Statistics protocols and is <br>subject to change due to internal data quality checking. Figures provided from <br>this source do not constitute part of National Statistics and should be treated <br>as provisional.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42248/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42248/answer",,,,,"1",,,"2014-03-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) men and (b) women who are victims of human trafficking are nationals of non-EEA countries have received return and reintegration assistance through the Assisted Voluntary Returns for Irregular Migrants programme since April 2011; and how much was so made available to those trafficked from (i) inside and (ii) outside the EU.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","191303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42249","Home Office","false","2014-04-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>This information is not available from Border Force systems.<br><br>Additionally, it is not in the interests of border and national security to disclose either the specific information held on Home Office Systems, or details relating to the volumes of data.</p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42249/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/42249/answer",,,,,"1",,,"2014-03-10",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of air passengers showing passports to UK Border agents are from Schengen area countries.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Mr Angus Brendan MacNeil","191203"
